{
  "texts": [
    "The performance of ML models is also assessed by statistical metrices.",
    "These metrices determine the accuracy level of the models in different aspects.",
    "The correlation between experimental and predicted results are measured using the correlation coefficient (R).",
    "R above 0.8 is considered a significant and robust correlation between the experimental and model-predicted results 91.",
    "However, R have shown insensitivity towards the division and multiplication of given outcomes 92."
  ]
}